## Changes

When a subprocessor is added, changed, or removed:

1. Update the table above (and the "Last reviewed" date).
2. Notify active customers per the privacy policy's "Changes" section if
   the change is material (new vendor, new data category, new region).
3. If the new vendor introduces a region outside the customer's
   expectation (e.g., a Canadian-data-residency customer and a US-based
   new vendor), notify those customers individually.
4. Record the change in the CHANGELOG with the date and reason.

## Vendor onboarding checklist

Before adding a vendor that will process personal information:

- [ ] Identify the data categories the vendor will receive.
- [ ] Confirm the vendor's processing region(s).
- [ ] Sign a data-processing agreement (or use vendor-default DPA terms
      after review).
- [ ] Review the vendor's security posture (SOC 2 Type II report,
      pen-test summary, or equivalent).
- [ ] If the vendor will process sensitive categories (health data,
      financial data), confirm BAA / DPA terms appropriate to the
      category.
- [ ] Add the vendor to this table.
- [ ] Notify customers per the privacy policy where required.

